title: How has mortality amenable to health care changed by gender?
analysis_commentary: Mortality rates for causes amenable to healthcare are higher in males than females. In 2010, this was a difference of 35.0 deaths per 100,000. The overall rate has decreased over time, from 202.9 in 1993 for all people to 88.1 in 2010, a decrease of 114.8 deaths per 100,000.
data_source: Health & Social Care Information Centre, Compendium of Population Health Indicators
